VenusOS-E3372h — Huawei E3372h modem support for Venus OS

This package adds full integration of the Huawei E3372h USB modem
(NCM stick mode, USB PID 12d1:1506) into Venus OS.

Features:
- D-Bus modem service (com.victronenergy.modem) with:
  Model, IMEI, NetworkName, NetworkType, SignalStrength,
  Connected, IP, SimStatus, RegStatus, Roaming
- NCM data connection via AT^NDISDUP + DHCP on wwan0
- Automatic hotplug: reconnects on USB replug
- Configurable APN via /data/e3372-config.conf
- Compatible with serial-starter and Venus OS GUI

Requirements:
- Venus OS v3.50 or later
- Huawei E3372h in NCM stick mode (USB PID 12d1:1506)
- SIM card with data plan
- SetupHelper package installed

Installation:
1. Install SetupHelper (if not already present)
2. Use PackageManager to add this package, or:
   cd /data
   git clone https://github.com/flmusic/VenusOS-E3372h.git
   /data/VenusOS-E3372h/setup install auto
3. Edit /data/e3372-config.conf with your APN
4. Reboot or re-run setup

Configuration:
Edit /data/e3372-config.conf:
  APN=your.operator.apn

Tested on:
- Raspberry Pi 3 Model B with Venus OS v3.72
- Bouygues Telecom (France), APN: mmsbouygtel.com
